title: 336.10-102 LAWS REPEALED; PROVISION FOR TRANSITION.
text:
(1) Minnesota Statutes 1961, Sections 48.29; 48.515; 48.518; 227.01 to 227.49; 227.56 to 227.59; 228.01 to 228.44; 228.52 to 228.55; 300.56; 302.01 to 302.22; 334.08; 334.09; 334.12; 335.01 to 335.03; 335.035 to 335.275; 335.276, as amended by Laws 1963, Chapter 301, Section 1; 335.28 to 335.80; 359.09; 359.10; 511.01 to 511.05; 511.06, as amended by Laws 1963, Chapter 173, Section 1; 511.07 to 511.32; 512.01 to 512.79; 513.12 to 513.19; 514.80 to 514.86; 514.87, as amended by Laws 1963, Chapter 59, Section 1; 514.88 to 514.91; 520.04 to 520.06; 521.01 to 521.07; 522.01 to 522.18; 601.02; and 601.03, are repealed.
(2) Transactions validly entered into before the effective date specified in section 336.10-105 and the rights, duties, and interests flowing from them remain valid thereafter and may be terminated, completed, consummated, or enforced as required or permitted by any statute or other law repealed by this chapter as though such repeal had not occurred.
